    "common_experiments_raw": "Yeast based assembly of large DNA payloads in yeast assembly vectors (YAVs) and verification by sequencing\nLanding pad installation and payload replacement using Cre mediated cassette exchange (RMCE) or CRISPR Cas9 based mSwAP In and related approaches\nHigh throughput and automated big DNA assembly workflows using JIB or SURE vectors and oligo pool derived linkers (OLIGARCHY)\nGenotyping and structural validation using targeted capture sequencing (Capture seq) plus whole genome sequencing when needed\nFunctional readouts including ATAC seq, RNA seq, CAGE seq, CUT and RUN and Hi C depending on the question\nPreclinical genome editing based disease modeling in mouse embryonic stem cells including TAF1 hybrid humanized alleles and CRISPRa rescue strategies"
